added that 1\nthe women must \"organise within the 1\nnext few years.\u201d\nWith the return of prosperity. In- 1\ndustries will clamor for women work\ners. In the opinion of Miss Mary E.\nMcDowell of the University of \u2018\u2019hirago\nSettlement house, who is chairman of 1\nthe women in industry I'ornmitteo of\nthe National league of Women Voters. 1\nTOOK CHIEF OF POLICE\nTO FIRE THE COOK\nI Tax Vega*, N M., Jan. R.\u2014A cook J\nemployed ln an exclusive residential 1\ndistrict was fired. Sho refused to\nj l*>av iFfforts of persuasion and then\nI threat* felled to make her budge from\n*he kitchen. Then Chief of police\nj Murphy was called.\n1 If .in Irish policeman has away\nI with women, it. wasn\u2019t demonstrated\nhere The conk greeted the chief with\n1 a pitcher of cold wafer Finally the\nchief persuaded her that she wasn't\nwanted.\nTRAPS GOLDEN EAGLE\nSheridan. Wyn., Jan. V -Catching\ngolden eagles. the monarch* of the \u2022\u00bbir.\n|ln coyote trap* in tho unusual exper\nloner of J. 1,. Taylor.\nTaylor art tho traps recently\nth*' Moore ranch, and was surprised\nwhen he visited them the following\nday to find two birds hold fast by their\ntors in itic* traps. One bird measures\nseven fort six inches from wine tip in\nwinii tip. tho other measures seven I\nfeet even. i\nBTJTTDAY, JANUARY 9, 1921\nTHE VALLEY. THE STATE. THE WEST\n4- The old reliable mining camp\nof Tollurlde and vicinity, ln tho\npast year of mining depression\nproduced oro to tho amount of\n4- MIGHT MJLJjION DOLLARS An\nV gold, silver, lead, copper, vana-\nilium ajtd camotltfi. Besides this\n4- there was large production from\n\u20224- fanning Industrie* of San\nMiguel county.\n\u2666\u2666rttt44t44444444444444t4^\n\u25a0KotryrrAi\u00dff road* out west\nSlightly more than six mllca of new\nconstruction work was done on for\nest service road projects within the\nBattloment National forest In tho cal\nendar year ID\u00b0o. This Include\" work on\ntho new road from Mesa to Mesa lake*\nand